   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CRYSTALLIZATION-STUDY OF THE GOSPEL OF GOD</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>in the Epistle to the Romans Message Four The Content of the Gospel of God</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>the Dynamic Salvation of God in Its Fullness The Essence of the Particular Items</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>of God s Dynamic Salvation Scripture Reading: Rom 1:16 OUTLINE The gospel of God is dynamic powerful to save all the sinners who would believe in it Rom 1:16: To redeem them: Judicially.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>By the blood of Christ Rom 3:24-25.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>On the cross 1 Pet 2:24a.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>From: Their sins Rev 1:5b.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>God s righteous judgment, wrath, and condemnation Rom 2:5-6, 16; 3:19b; John 3:18b.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The eternal perdition in the lake of fire Rev 21:8; 22:15.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The accusation of Satan, God s enemy cf.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Rev 12:10-11.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Through: The forgiveness of sins Eph 1:7.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The washing of the believing sinners sins Rev 1:5b; 1 Cor 6:11.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The reconciliation of the believing sinners to God from their enmity toward God Rom 5:10a.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The justification of the believing sinners by God Rom 3:20-24.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The making of peace between the believing sinners and God Rom 5:1.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The sanctification of the believing sinners unto God positionally Heb 10:10, 14, 29b; 13:12a.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Such a redemption lays the foundation of God s dynamic salvation for the consummation of God s dynamic salvation.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>To save them: Organically.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>By the life of Christ Rom 5:10b.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>In the Spirit of life Rom 8:2.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>From: The indwelling sin Rom 7:17; 8:2.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>The condemnation due to the sinful action of the indwelling sin Rom 7:17-20; 8:1.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>The old man Rom 6:6.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>The natural I Gal 2:20a.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>The self Matt 16:24.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>The flesh with its passions and its lusts Gal 5:24.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>Worldliness 1 John 2:15-16; Rom 12:2a.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Tribulations and all kinds of environmental troubles Rom 5:3; 8:35-39.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Spiritual death and weakness Rom 8:5, 7, 24-26; Rev 3:1-2.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>The vanity and the slavery of corruption Rom 8:20-21.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>Through: Regeneration, washing the believers from the oldness of their old man Titus 3:5a and making them the many sons of God 1 Pet 1:3; John 3:3, 5; 1:12-13; Heb 2:10.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>The dispositional sanctification Rom 6:19, 22; 15:16b; 1 Thes 5:23.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>Renewing Titus 3:5b; Rom 12:2b.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>Transformation to change the believers constitution metabolically with the divine element of the life of Christ into His image from glory to glory Rom 12:2b; 2 Cor 3:18: 1 Making the believers boast in their tribulations Rom 5:3.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>2 Making the believers more than conquerors over the environmental troubles Rom 8:35-39.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>3 Making the believers kings to reign in the eternal life through the abounding grace Rom 5:17, 21.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>Conformation, conforming them to the image of Christ as the firstborn Son of God to be the mass reproduction of Jesus the God-man as the prototype for the building up of His organic Body Rom 8:29.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>Glorification, the redemption of the believers body, to glorify the believers in their entire being with the divine glory for their full enjoyment of their divine sonship Rom 8:23, 30.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>Such a salvation consummates the building up of the church, the organic Body of Christ fully covered by the following chapters 12 16, after the parenthetical section of chapters 9 11 , which will consummate in the New Jerusalem as the center of the eternal economy of God.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>The way to partake of the dynamic salvation of God: Believing in your heart that God has raised Jesus the Lord from the dead Rom 10:9b.</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>Confessing with your mouth Jesus as Lord and calling upon the name of the Lord Rom 10:9a, 13.</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>To be baptized into Christ Jesus, the embodiment of the Triune God the Father, the Son, and the Spirit , to get into the organic union with the Triune God embodied in Christ Rom 6:3; Matt 28:19.</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>Now that we have seen the center of the gospel of God, we want to go on to see its content.</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>The content of the gospel of God is the dynamic salvation of God in its fullness.</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>In this message we want to see the essence of the particular items of God s dynamic salvation.</S>
   </TEXT>
